CONCLUSIONS: Patients who present after total but oncologically inadequate 
excision of STS can receive approximately 50 Gy before re-resection or 
approximately 60 Gy after re-resection, with approximately equivalent, 
satisfactory local control and overall disease outcome. Decisions as to the most 
appropriate treatment sequence for any individual patient can be made regardless 
of considerations as to the effectiveness of one sequence compared with the 
other.

