Introduction to health economics for the medical practitioner.

Kernick DP(1).

Author information:
(1)St Thomas' Medical Group, Exeter, UK. su1838@eclipse.co.uk

Against a background of increasing demands on limited resources, health 
economics is exerting an influence on decision making at all levels of health 
care. Health economics seeks to facilitate decision making by offering an 
explicit decision making framework based on the principle of efficiency. It is 
not the only consideration but it is an important one and practitioners will 
