Does dietary sugar and fat influence longevity?

Archer VE(1).

Author information:
(1)Department of Family and Preventive Medicine, University of Utah, Salt Lake 
City, Utah 84112-5120, USA. varcher@dfpm.utah.edu

Simultaneous consideration of the influence of the different types of 
carbohydrates and fats in human diets on mortality rates (especially the 
diseases of aging), and the probable retardation of such diseases by caloric 
restriction (CR) leads to the hypothesis that restriction of foods with a high 
glycemic index and saturated or hydrogenated fats would avoid or delay many 
diseases of aging and might result in life extension. Many of the health 
benefits of CR might thereby be available to humans without the side effects or 
unacceptability of semi-starvation diets.

